    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but it's more than just \"signaling.\" when u look at the frequency, the discrepancies in the metadata don't just move info, they move actual purchasing power. like, if a specific metadata string is present in a series of trades, the settlement value of the associated assets fluctuates in a way that looks mathematically tied to the metadata itself. it feels less like a signal and more like the metadata IS the asset. if the traditional auditors are only looking at the fiat side, aren't they basically blind to the real movement of wealth?",
